Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.23,0:03:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:234234,236169}Isabelle, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.50,0:03:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:236503,238038}Go ahead of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:239806,241141}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.87,0:04:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:245879,247447}Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.71,0:04:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:251718,253386}We're leaving, fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.46,0:04:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:263463,265031}Jean, we're ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.03,0:04:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:265031,266466}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:278044,280580}Isabelle, we must\Ndetach the chain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288655,290090}All right, I'll row!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:291858,294828}You can do it, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.82,0:04:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:294828,296763}Faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.28,0:05:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:313280,315148}Do you think we can make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.14,0:05:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:315148,319419}So far, everything worked out.\NIt'll be fine. Don't worry, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.05,0:05:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:320053,321655}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.12,0:05:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:327127,331331}{\i1}Meanwhile, in Versailles …
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.09,0:05:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:332098,335268}Mr. Thiers, why\Ndid you flee Paris?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.76,0:05:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:335769,340740}After losing the capital, our troops have lost\Ntheir morale and are in disarray now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.04,0:05:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:341041,345912}I would appreciate it if you did not\Nblame me for your own failures.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.91,0:05:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:345912,349416}It is you who did not manage to gather\Nthe army, contrary to what you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:349416,351585}How do you intend\Nto take responsibility for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:351952,356957}Further conversation is pointless. I don't\Nwant to talk to a coward like you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.39,0:06:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:360393,363096}Are you resigning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:363096,365098}I am sorry to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.89,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365899,367434}General Gambetta…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.44,0:06:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376443,381781}Sir, what will happen\Nto France now without you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:382082,389189}Victor. There is no shame in executing orders\Nissued by an incompetent government.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:389823,393293}Soldiers must obey\Nthe orders they're given.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393293,399199}Even if the order is wrong, the military\Nmust comply with it and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:446646,452218}In this war, thousands\Nof soldiers gave their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.21,0:07:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452218,458458}Perhaps death on the battlefield\Nwas their destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.45,0:07:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:458458,462896}But when you look\Nat each of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.89,0:07:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:462896,468101}when you take their uniforms off,\Nyou'll see a loving man in each.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.10,0:07:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:468101,473807}Each of them had someone he loved:\Nparents, children, siblings or a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.80,0:07:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:473807,476476}Nonetheless, they left them\Nand went to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.15,0:08:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:488154,490123}The fate of their homeland\Nafter their death
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.12,0:08:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:490123,492959}is the only reward for their efforts,\Nand a very small one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.95,0:08:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:492959,498999}However, when their death serves\Nonly Thiers and his interests,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.99,0:08:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:498999,503970}I can't be called anything other than\Na traitor who has betrayed their trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.97,0:08:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:503970,507374}My resignation\Nis the only right choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.37,0:08:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:507374,511911}It is also compensation\Nfor those who died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.91,0:08:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:511911,514948}How about you? What are you\Ngoing to do, Captain Langlois?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.94,0:08:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:514948,516950}I am a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:516950,522122}No matter what the order is,\Nthe soldier must carry it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.12,0:08:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:522122,527727}It is not my role to decide\Nwhether the order is correct or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.72,0:08:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527727,530797}You yourself said so just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:530797,534067}I understand.\NThat is also a way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.06,0:08:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534067,536736}This is where our paths part,\NCaptain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.73,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:536736,539606}Remember to always\Nvalue your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.85,0:09:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:554854,558491}{\i1}It's the only way to live I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.49,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:558491,560493}{\i1}That's who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.46,0:09:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:563463,570103}{\i1}The next day, Victor\Nhappened to see a wanted poster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.10,0:09:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:570103,574107}{\i1}In it, there was Isabelle's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.42,0:09:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589422,593893}Jean, don't you think\Nthat we're not moving at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.06,0:09:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:594060,598765}There's nothing we can do about it.\NThere's no wind. Take a sit and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.76,0:10:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:598765,602335}There's nothing to rave about.\NSooner or later it'll blow and we'll sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.23,0:10:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603236,606005}Boy, you are reckless, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.00,0:10:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:606005,610210}I need to deliver this letter\Nas soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.87,0:10:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:610877,612812}I was so waiting for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.81,0:10:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:612812,614280}For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:614280,617817}To see your anger.\NYou're so beautiful when you're mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.81,0:10:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:617817,621588}And this short cut?\NIt suits you perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.58,0:10:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:621588,623857}I think I fell in love\Nwith you all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.85,0:10:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:623857,626626}You crack me up.\NI've had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.62,0:10:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:626626,629896}You have a lot of nerve to joke around\Nunder such circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.43,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:630430,634467}It is best to joke around\Nin such situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:634467,637804}The wheel of fortune will turn either way.\NWhat matters is your mood when it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.80,0:10:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:637804,639906}You are so—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.90,0:10:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:639906,641908}Ah! It's a ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.90,0:10:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:641908,645078}– Look, a ship!\N– I told you so! Ahoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.07,0:10:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:645078,650316}It's a British flag! They must be coming home\Nfrom France. They can take us on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.31,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650316,655722}– Ahoy! We need help!\N– We're here! – Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.72,0:10:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:655722,657690}Hooray, they noticed us!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.69,0:10:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:657690,659792}They did!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.79,0:11:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:659792,662428}– We're saved!\N– Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.07,0:11:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:674073,676009}Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.00,0:11:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:676009,678144}Isabelle, can you swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679512,681247}Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:690290,691758}Jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.82,0:12:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:720820,723456}What on earth\Nis wrong with this ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:723456,726226}Yes, something is\Ndefinitely wrong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.09,0:12:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:733099,734500}He got me good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.56,0:12:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:735568,736936}Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:736936,738304}Gotcha.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.74,0:12:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:748748,749916}It's him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.91,0:12:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:749916,753353}Are you kidding me!?\NSo much for the ship…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.49,0:12:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757490,760593}No, it's too early to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.79,0:12:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:765798,767634}You monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.23,0:12:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769235,770603}Catch me if you can!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.64,0:13:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:777644,780079}We meet again,\NMr. Petty Officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.85,0:13:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:819852,821921}Run, Isabelle! Run away!
Comment: 0,0:13:53.80,0:13:53.80,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:833800,833800}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.67,0:14:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:840673,843443}Isabelle, behind you!\NClimb that ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844077,845978}Climb it!\NGo up, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.48,0:14:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:851484,853720}What should I do?!\NOh, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.83,0:14:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:864831,867333}Hang in there, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.61,0:14:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:878611,881114}Almost there, Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.48,0:14:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:887487,889789}– Isabelle! I'm coming to you!\N– Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.29,0:15:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:900299,901701}Isabelle, jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.72,0:15:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:920720,922054}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.45,0:15:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922455,924223}We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.22,0:15:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:924223,925858}Hooray!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:925858,928094}Jean!\NYou were wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.26,0:15:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:929262,931864}Hey, Isabelle.\NHere, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:931864,935001}No. One must suffice.\NYou're so greedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.43,0:15:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:936436,938404}She likes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.19,0:16:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:958191,964030}{\i1}Soon in the sky appeared gulls,\Na sign that they were approaching land.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.03,0:16:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:964030,968100}{\i1}The crew's eyes\Nlaid on jagged cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:968100,972805}{\i1}Isabelle and Jean saw\Nthe British soil for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.17,0:16:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976175,977109}Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.10,0:16:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:977109,978544}Hm? Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.24,0:16:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:980246,981714}How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.31,0:16:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:983316,984817}So? How do I look?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.48,0:16:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:986486,990289}Just perfect! You look good\Nin everything, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.49,0:16:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:991491,992692}Thank you, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:999532,1000967}You've changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1000967,1004837}You really think so?\NYes, I guess I have, a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004837,1008608}They say there's no progress\Nwithout change.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.87,0:16:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1009876,1015381}But I don't get you, Jean.\NWhy are you chasing after me so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.38,0:17:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1015381,1022221}I'm a terrible tomboy. Apart from\Nstrength, I have no good points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.22,0:17:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022221,1025491}I've never had anyone but you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.56,0:17:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1030563,1034600}I'd always been\Nweak, shy and timid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.60,0:17:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034600,1036602}You always had had to\Nsave me from trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.23,0:17:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1038237,1043075}You'd been my\Nonly friend back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.07,0:17:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1043075,1045811}I'd thought\NI'd never wanted to lose you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.34,0:17:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1047346,1051150}Fencing… Shooting…\NHorse riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051150,1053352}I learned it all because\NI was interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.72,0:17:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054720,1057957}That's… just who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.35,0:17:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060359,1062728}{\i1}Isabelle, you'll be my bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.39,0:17:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1064397,1066666}{\i1}Who'd like to marry\Nsuch a weakling?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.76,0:17:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067767,1070036}{\i1}I am not a weakling!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.97,0:17:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1072972,1074674}{\i1}Learn to respect a lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1085985,1088854}But… you see, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.25,0:18:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1089255,1091257}I know already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.99,0:18:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1091991,1095161}Just as I adore you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.16,0:18:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095161,1098864}you've hated me\Nall this time as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.33,0:18:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1100333,1104570}It's not easy to change the feelings\Nthat have been in us since childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.57,0:18:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104570,1107573}But I will make you\Nfall in love with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.87,0:18:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109875,1111744}Some day. You will see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.84,0:18:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1112845,1115081}Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.58,0:18:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1115581,1118985}Because if I don't,\NI'll be very, very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.98,0:18:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1118985,1120753}Sniff… Just kidding, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.75,0:18:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1120753,1122855}I know all too well\Nthat tears don't work on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124924,1128928}Jean, why do you always joke\Nand belittle yourself so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.92,0:18:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1128928,1134500}It's just that if I don't do that,\NI think I'd die from embarrassment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.00,0:18:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1135001,1137403}Sorry if I interrupt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138204,1143342}We will reach the Dover shore soon.\NWe have prepared a boat for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.70,0:19:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1143709,1144710}A boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.71,0:19:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144710,1147079}You are illegal immigrants.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.07,0:19:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1147079,1148748}Illegal?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.98,0:19:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1148981,1154286}Yes. But if you steal this boat and disappear,\Nthere's nothing we can do, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.15,0:19:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1155154,1156656}Mister…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1156656,1157790}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.79,0:19:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160793,1162461}Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.46,0:19:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162461,1163996}Sail safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.66,0:19:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1168668,1170236}Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1170236,1172672}– Goodbye!\N– Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.52,0:19:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1188521,1192224}So, young lady, you're about to\Ntake your first step on the British soil.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.22,0:19:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1192224,1194360}Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1222555,1227359}{\i1}The night after Isabelle\Nand Jean landed in England,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.35,0:20:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227359,1231297}{\i1}they reached\Ntheir destination: London.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.19,0:20:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1232198,1235768}Let's look… SE9, SE10.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235768,1237002}Are you sure of this address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237002,1240806}Yes, I am.\NDomino Street, SE 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240806,1244043}Over there is 12, there 13…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.44,0:20:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1248447,1251383}Two lads. Two lads!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.38,0:20:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1251383,1254253}Look carefully.\NOne of them may be in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.78,0:20:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254787,1257957}They both look like\Nplain boys to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.42,0:21:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258424,1260793}– Watch their every move.\N– Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.43,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1264430,1266298}– We're here.\N– Awesome. Let's knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1266298,1267600}Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1271003,1271971}It'll take a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.97,0:21:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1271971,1273572}Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274573,1277109}He took out a compact!\NIt's a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.11,0:21:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278110,1280246}Just like I suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.24,0:21:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1280246,1281947}Very well. Shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.61,0:21:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286619,1287787}Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.78,0:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1287787,1289855}I won't let you hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.85,0:21:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1289855,1291690}Gaston?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.69,0:21:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291690,1294860}Look, it's our\Nwould-be dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.86,0:21:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1294860,1298264}Thanks for saving me the effort\Nof searching for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.26,0:21:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298264,1302301}Let me deal with you before\NI take care of the girl. Kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.30,0:21:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1302301,1302935}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.10,0:21:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307106,1308641}What an vigorous old man!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.98,0:21:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314980,1316849}There is nowhere to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.82,0:22:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1322822,1325624}Panza! Welcome to London.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.89,0:22:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326892,1328961}Who are you, you rubes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.96,0:22:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328961,1331564}I am Count Red,\Nand this is my shadow army.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.69,0:22:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332698,1334300}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.60,0:22:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1335601,1340005}Panza. I suggest you\Nto retreat voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.71,0:22:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1348714,1350449}{\i1}Where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1354587,1357590}Count Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1359959,1362061}What do you want?\NIt's the middle of the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.43,0:22:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1364430,1367967}Does someone by the name\Nof Martin Schmidt live here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.96,0:22:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1367967,1370369}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.10,0:22:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1369101,1371837}{\an8}Mom, where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.36,0:22:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1370369,1374306}Quiet! If you eat everything,\Nyour butt is doomed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.64,0:22:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375641,1379578}We were sent by Jules from Paris.\NWhere can we find Mr. Schmidt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.57,0:23:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1379578,1381914}Knowing him, he's probably\Nguzzling beer in a pub again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1381914,1382615}In a pub?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.61,0:23:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1382615,1386986}His favorite is called "Max In".\NMake sure to check there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1394860,1399331}{\i1}At that time, London was a refuge\Nfor revolutionaries, thinkers,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.33,0:23:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1399331,1403936}{\i1}and tramps looking for a way\Nto earn some extra money.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.93,0:23:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1403936,1410276}{\i1}These people spent their free time\Ngathering and hanging out in pubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.27,0:23:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1410276,1413879}{\i1}Max In was one of those pubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.15,0:23:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1421153,1427226}{\i1}Isabelle felt a strange emotion\Nshe had never experienced before,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.22,0:23:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1427226,1429595}{\i1}as she stood shocked,\Nlooking at this alien environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.69,0:23:57.53,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1432698,1437536}{\fad(400,200)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur1\fs20\an5\pos(575,418)\t(4338,4838,5,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
Comment: 0,0:23:58.37,0:23:58.37,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1438370,1438370}Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.37,0:24:00.53,Default,(sign),0,0,0,,{TIME:1438370,1440539}Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.07,0:24:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1441073,1445878}We arrived in the city of fogs, London,\Nand we got to meet Mr. Schmidt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.87,0:24:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1445878,1449181}Panza, however,\Ngives us no peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.18,0:24:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1449181,1453485}Then suddenly\NVictor makes his appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.48,0:24:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1453485,1455754}Next time on "Isabelle of Paris":
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.75,0:24:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1455754,1458324}"Love Burning in The Night Fog".\NPlease look forward to it.
Comment: 0,0:24:18.32,0:24:18.32,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:1458324,1458324}Ending
